<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-275-218  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 275 218.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  March 13 1989 v3 n11 p31(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Rep. Mavroules to DOD: adopt Packard Commission proposals.andO;(Nicholas Mavroules)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taylor, Kimberly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Rep.andP;  Nicholas Mavroules is urging Pentagon officials to adopt therecommendations of the Packard Commission in an effort to lowercosts and increase efficiency.andP;  The Packard Commission, in 1986,recommended that the Department of Defense's acquisition system bestreamlined with the addition of an undersecretary foracquisitions.andP;  Following the practices of private industry andsharing equipment are ways to further cut costs.andP;  Under theleadership of a strong secretary of Defense, the department'sinefficiency could be brought under control.andP;  Mavroules also wantsthe command, control, communications and intelligence structure tobe strengthened, and will demand that government contractorsconduct their business ethically.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseManagementBudgetingReorganizationGovernment ContractsUnited States. Presidential Commission on Defense Management.andO;Person:    Mavroules, Nicholas (political activity).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>